During the special period, Wuhan has become a city where people all over the country are concerned and pray for good fortune. What was the real life of the people of Wuhan after the city closure?

Let's take a look at Wuhan on the 25th.

First, after 24 provincial medical teams entered Wuhan, a large number of military medical teams in Wuhan on the 25th to carry out rescue work.

The National Health Commission set up six medical rescue teams with a total of 1,230 people to assist Wuhan, and at the same time called up six reserve echelons on standby. Three medical teams from Shanghai, Guangdong and the army have arrived in Wuhan and are ready to work.

The military medical teams are drawn from the Military Medical Universities of the Army, Navy and Air Force with 150 personnel each, divided into a command group, a general patient treatment team and a critical care team, equipped with smoking, infectious diseases, hospital infection control, intensive-care unit and other medical experts, many of whom have participated in Xiaotangshan anti-sars, anti-egyptian aid experience.

The general public is applauding. The experts from other provinces and the PLA medical team came, and the people of Wuhan were even more relieved. One thing I shouldn't have said, but as soon as Zhong Nanshan left that day, my heart beat like a drum: Why did you leave? Everything we do now, he suggests or thinks about.

Although Wuhan is a key medical town, last year, Tongji, Xiehe, people, China-South Africa, Wuhan University Dental hospitals into the top 100 hospitals, but, in such a virus war, it is clearly unsustainable.

Here's another problem. The cities around Wuhan are also among the most dangerous. Local netizens raised the question of "dark under the lamp" , that is, Wuhan is dangerous, the city around Wuhan is "separated by a wall" , it is also dangerous, protective supplies are also very short, the anti-virus force is even weaker. Xiantao hospital has also put up a notice to accept donations. This should arouse the great attention of Hubei provincial leaders.

Prevention and control of "new pneumonia" in Wuhan City Circle.

Two, the long-distance treatment is going to go for a walk.

Since the 25th, the Yangtze River Network Wuhan City Message Board officially opened 24-hour online consultation, the first batch of 20 experts have been assembled. It includes more than 200 doctors and specialists in the Wuhan area and in the whole country, including the departments of smoking, digestive medicine, cardiovascular medicine, neurology, nephrology, infection, gynecology, obstetrics, pediatrics, emergency department, ent, ophthalmology, dermatology and psychology, the formation of an expert advisory team, timely online to answer questions from the public. Representative questions will also be answered in the Yangtze Daily and Wuhan Evening News.

This is the combination of online and offline in medicine.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Wuhan's online Ministry of Mass Work -- Foshan Citizen Message Board was a great creation in 2017. I leave a message whenever I have a problem, and the problem will be solved soon. Later there was enterprise direct, reflecting the problems encountered by enterprises. It's now used for online consultations, where you don't touch, you don't see each other, you solve medical problems. You can learn in a foreign country.

Why can't we hear the Houx Internet hospital at this hour? COME OUT AND TAKE A walk!

Third, commandeer hospitals and hotels.

On the 24th, the provincial Party secretary called on Wuhan to use all levels of power to increase the number of isolation observation places and designated hospital beds, to treat all suspected patients unconditionally, and to carry out effective isolation, strengthen classified diagnosis and treatment, and optimize the diagnosis and treatment process, ensure that patients with fever receive prompt treatment.

The first, second and third batch of hospitals in Wuhan were requisitioned on March 25 from two designated hospitals and 61 fever clinics, following the basic requirements of infectious disease prevention and treatment institutions, temporarily converted into a hospital for patients with fever.

There are currently more than 4,000 beds for suspected and confirmed cases. Another 6,000 beds will be made available by the end of this month. The fourth batch of hospitals will be requisitioned in time according to the development of the epidemic situation. That's reassuring.

Where do so many local and foreign medical personnel live?

Local hoteliers in Wuhan organized the "Wuhan Medical Hotel Support Group" on Thursday to solicit air conditioning hotels to volunteer to provide free accommodation for frontline medical staff in major hospitals in the city.

At present, the hotel which can provide free accommodation for medical staff covers 11 districts including Hongshan district, Wuchang District district, Hankou district, Hanyang District district, Caidian District district, etc. . The number of hotels supported by Hongshan District and Wuchang districts is relatively large, with more than 30 hotels already fully occupied, while the Hankou district is the most short of accommodation.

At present, more than 100 hotels have joined the situation of full occupancy or even over-occupancy, some support hotels have also been requisitioned as a quarantine observation area. Therefore, "Wuhan Medical Hotel Support Group" crowd advocate Hoo, hope to have more hotel owners to join the activities.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The key moment, has manifested the entrepreneur's social sense of responsibility and the selfless dedication spirit. Let's give them a thumbs up. Thank you, Wuhan!

The fourth is to build a "new type of pneumonia" treatment hospital.

At 3:30 pm on the 25th, the COVID-19 of pneumonia in Wuhan decided to build a new "Little Tangshan Hospital" -- Foshan, in Wuhan, in addition to the Caidian District Fire Mountain Hospital, within half a month, 1,300 additional beds.

Fire and thunder, working together to fight COVID-19 pneumonia. It shows that Wuhan is getting more and more efficient.

Fifth, "with the CAR" and "sealed the car.

On the 24th, Wuhan issued the new pneumonia prevention and control headquarters circular No. 8. The circular pointed out that in order to solve the problems of residents'travel inconvenience at home, the city has called for an urgent call for 6,000 taxis, which will be allocated to the central urban area and used by the unified dispatch of the Community Neighborhood Committees, provide door-to-door food delivery, medicine delivery and food delivery services for the residents who live in the community with inconvenience.

By the afternoon of the 25th, the list of districts had been drawn up. 10 central urban districts (7 administrative districts and 3 functional districts, namely Jingkai, East L. and scenic area) with a total of 1159 communities. Wuhan's Transport Bureau has launched an emergency plan, calling nine tour and online taxi companies to deploy and commandeer 6,000 taxis (at least four in each community) .

I have seen the cab number, driver's name, mobile phone number of our community, as well as the community grid member, property management information, if something to contact them.

Get up in the afternoon and see an even more stunning message -- lock up in central city. From "Road Block" to "Road Block" , this is too fast!

In order to control the risk of infection caused by the movement of people, starting from 00:00 on January 26,2020, the central urban area will be closed to vehicular traffic except for authorized transportation vehicles, free transportation vehicles and official vehicles. If you need to go out, you can find a community taxi.

The shock of the news was too great.

Soon, many citizens took to the streets, straight to the supermarket, there was a "panic buying wave. ". Netizens reported that some places were a little nervous about sharing bicycles.

Immediately, two very different views emerged on the web:

Some citizens think, do not let the private car on the street, how citizens shopping, how to get medical treatment? Is that really necessary? A private car is a relatively enclosed space.

Some citizens also expressed their understanding. The idea was to limit the number of people who could go to the hospital. You can take a government-provided taxi if you have important business.

In any case, there will be no private cars on Wuhan Road, which is a once-in-a-lifetime thing.

Finally, let's take a look at the national situation.

As of 2400 hours on January 25, the National Health Commission has received a total of 1,975 confirmed cases and 324 severe cases from 30 provinces (autonomous regions and municipalities) . There were 56 death cases and 49 cured cases. There are currently 2,684 suspected cases.

Let us remember the number of cold deaths on the first day of the New Year -- as many as 56. What all the Chinese are doing is making the death toll grow a little slower, a little slower, until it reaches zero.

As of 15:00 on the 25th, a total of 24 provinces, municipalities and autonomous regions across the country had launched the first-level response to major public health emergencies, covering a total population of more than 1.2 billion people. That's a rare number in the world.

It turns out that only 1.6 billion people in the world have a per capita GDP of more than $10,000. China reached that figure in 2019, so overnight, 3 billion people in the world have a per capita GDP of more than $10,000.

That was Wen's Law: In an exclusive interview with The Washington Post in November 2003, Premier Wen Jiabao first revealed his "simple but complex multiplication and division" to the public, that is, "a very small problem, multiplied by 1.3 billion, becomes a big problem; a very large amount, divided by 1.3 billion, becomes a small number. ".

According to the nature, degree of harm and scope of public health emergencies, public health emergencies are classified into four levels: especially significant (grade I) , significant (Grade II) , relatively large (Grade III) and general (Grade IV) . Where the level I response is the highest level response. The provincial headquarters shall, in accordance with the decision-making and unified command of the State Council, organize and coordinate the emergency handling work within its own administrative area.

For example, in my hometown of Fujian, all personnel of vehicles heading for Fujian are checked one by one. Starting from 10:30 on January 25, the first day of the first lunar month, the entrance to the Fuding of the Shenhai expressway is closed, and the exit of the expressway is only accessible, for vehicles heading to Fuzhou, please take the bypass railway to exit the eight-foot Gate Expressway. For vehicles heading to Zhejiang, please exit the Fuding North (Bangfu expressway) or Fenshuguan expressway.

A few days ago, we are still shocked Wuhan "closed city" , now they are also heavily armed, the city on alert, and Wuhan is almost.

I would also like to appeal to friends around the kindness of Wuhan People.

In some places, for example, the people of Henan have understandably poured dirt on the roads that connect them to Hubei, creating a roadblock. However, it is not good for gas stations not to allow vehicles in Hubei to refuel. We have to refuel before we can leave. In some places, it is unreasonable not to let guests stay in Wuhan, Hubei.

Let me conclude by saying. According to the situation on the 25th, external rescue forces entered Wuhan, the control measures in Wuhan became more and more effective, the fear in society decreased, and a pattern of co-prevention and co-management was formed in the whole country.

Finally, there is a real "one heart, one mind, " the atmosphere, from the day of victory is getting closer and closer.
